# Journal Content Conventions

- Keep `summary` useful as a meta description: one concise sentence, generally 140-170 characters when practical.
- Include the day location in `location`; include recognizable place names in `summary` when they help sharing/search.
- Use simple, place-aware image alt text based on nearby text: `[subject/action] at/in [location]`.
- Prefer concrete alts like `Canoes on Chesterfield Reservoir in Idaho` over generic alts like `Another view`, `More displays`, or `IMG_1234`.
- For signs, markers, museums, and historic sites, name the location or subject: `Fort Bridger entrance sign`, `Oregon Buttes viewed from the trail route`.
- Do not over-describe decorative details; alt text should explain why the image is in the journal.
